data.name: Death's Door
data.description: Reaping souls of the dead and punching a clock might get monotonous but it's honest work for a Crow. The job gets lively when your assigned soul is stolen and you must track down a desperate thief to a realm untouched by death - where creatures grow far past their expiry.

recommends.name: The Legend of Zelda™: Breath of the Wild

comments.content: I’m honestly a little shocked at how much gushing there is over Death’s Door. It’s not a bad game, and there’s clearly a lot of love and care gone into the presentation. It’s just not terribly interesting.

A good game that I regret buying.

This game is very well made and looks nice. Its very clean and polished and I suspect many people will love it.
However for me all that polish did is keep me invested long enough that i could no longer return the game once I realized it wasn't something I wanted.

One of the best games I've ever played. It's basically Breath of the Wild meets a souls-like, but you play as a crow. The combat is challenging but not super hard, and the music and atmosphere are incredible. Highly recommend.

Very sweet game! If you like the classig Zelda games, you will also like Death's Door. You will meet enjoyable characters, the art style is fantastic and the gameplay is really smooth. The combat is not complex at all and it's fair. If you still die once in a while, there is always a respawn point (doors) nearby. Overall a perfect game for people who just want to take a break, relax and have a fun little adventure.
      If you pay a little attention you will notice that there is more stuff hidden in the game, waiting to be discovered.

Best indie game i have played this year.
  +Extremely fun combat
  +Great story and characters
  +Amazing art style
  +Amazing soundtrack
  I cant recommend this enough, seriously give it a shot if you like hack and slash RPG's <3
